"editors may encounter when working on representing information on GRSciColl."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: en/grscicoll/modules/ROOT/pages/recommendations.adoc:11
#, no-wrap
msgid "How to represent sub-collections?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/grscicoll/modules/ROOT/pages/recommendations.adoc:15
msgid ""
"In some cases, institutions might be interested in highlighting a particular "
"subset of collections. For example, historical or private collections that "
"have been integrated in a larger collection.  Institutions always have the "
"possibility to create separate collection entries for those. However, some "
"alternatives are available:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/grscicoll/modules/ROOT/pages/recommendations.adoc:17
msgid ""
"You can use the “incorporated collections” field to emphasise collections "
"that were integrated in a larger one."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/grscicoll/modules/ROOT/pages/recommendations.adoc:18
msgid ""
"Sub-collection codes can also be added as alternative codes of a collection "
"entry."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/grscicoll/modules/ROOT/pages/recommendations.adoc:19
msgid ""
"The collection descriptor groups can be used to structure sub-collections. "
"For example, you can create one collection descriptor group per sub-"
"collections with its own title and description."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: en/grscicoll/modules/ROOT/pages/recommendations.adoc:20
#, no-wrap
msgid "How to share literature references associated with a collection or its specimens?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/grscicoll/modules/ROOT/pages/recommendations.adoc:23
msgid ""
"There is no ideal way to currently share literature references associated "
"with a collection or its specimens. For now, we recommend sharing such "
"references as collection descriptors. For example, the https://scientific-"
"collections.gbif.org/collection/"
"d4e9aa65-7974-4a31-9b0c-817d474294bc[Japanese Antartic meteorite collection] "
"has a set of references mapped to the Darwin core term https://dwc.tdwg.org/"
"terms/#dcterms:bibliographicCitation[bibliographicCitation]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/grscicoll/modules/ROOT/pages/recommendations.adoc:26
msgid "We will update the training documentation as guidelines are developed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: en/grscicoll/modules/ROOT/pages/recommendations.adoc:27
#, no-wrap
msgid "How to represent virtual collections?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/grscicoll/modules/ROOT/pages/recommendations.adoc:30
msgid ""
"GRSciColl was not designed to represent virtual collections. If you wish to "
"create metrics for a subset of specimen related records published on GBIF, "
"consider selecting the occurrences based on their associated data (for "
"example, their scientific names). If you are publishing occurrences shared "
"on GBIF, consider using Darwin Core terms like https://dwc.tdwg.org/terms/"
"#dwc:datasetID[datasetID] for occurrences to facilitate their selection."
msgstr ""
